data.name: label2.Text
data.value:
With its historical texture, colorful nightlife, narrow streets and artistic activities, the capital of Berlin, Germany is at the top of the list of places to visit.
Potsdamer Square, which gained importance after the fall of the Berlin Wall in 1989, attracts attention.
In the square reflecting the bohemian spirit of Europe, you can visit the shopping centers or take a walk on the colorful streets. You can visit historical monuments such as the Berliner Dom, the Brandenburg Gate, the Gendarmenmarkt, the Bellevue Palace, the Olympiastadion and the Charlottenburg Palace.
